title: ICE: Normalizing Binder without wrapping in a Binder

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

body:
### Code [Library version (choose "Build" from the pulldown):](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=f340049395bb2407b90ac46c5e243471) ```Rust // Compile as library fn h5(_: T) where for<'x> fn(&'x u32): Fn(&'x u32), { } ``` [Binary version:](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=43e99506a54b2e64f9ebc56d5520dd0b) ```Rust // Compile as binary fn h5(_: T) where for<'x> fn(&'x u32): Fn(&'x u32), { } fn main(){ h5(|_|{}) } ``` The two have (slightly) differing output. **Note:** If you compile as a binary but don't call the problematic function, compilation succeeds. Compiling as a library ICEs even when the function is private. ### Meta * Stable Playground 1.59.0 * Beta Playground 1.60.0-beta.5 (2022-03-18 6ee5a408a3bbc7659863) * Nightly Playground 1.61.0-nightly (2022-03-19 8d60bf427a4b055f4641) * Godbolt 1.42.0 -- present (spot checked) ### Error output #### Library version ``` warning: function is never used: `h5` [--> src/lib.rs:1:4 ](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021#) | 1 | fn h5(_: T) | ^^ | = note: `#[warn(dead_code)]` on by defaulterror: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc ### Version it worked on [Works on `1.41.0`.](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/aT6z6ehxe) Works on versions prior to this down to [`1.7.0`](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/e5nf31rzj) (spot checked). (Version [`1.6.0`](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/fdPPbnazG) gives obsoleted error [`E0193`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/error-index.html#E0193).) ### Versions with regression Versions [`1.42.0`](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/6qzMjsb4o) and up (spot checked). The error changes between [`1.54.0`](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/ebMq6acr8) and [`1.55.0`](https://rust.godbolt.org/z/WccE9GdEz). @rustbot modify labels: +regression-from-stable-to-stable -regression-untriaged
